<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p><a href="">www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2253.txt</a>" rel="nofollow"&gt;RFC 2253 says:</p>

<p>Implementations MUST allow a semicolon character to be used instead
of a comma to separate RDNs in a distinguished name, and MUST also
allow whitespace characters to be present on either side of the comma
or semicolon.</p>

<p>Currently the _isDnString method is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
protected function _isDnString($str)
{
    return $str &amp;&amp; stristr($str, ',DC=');
}
</code></pre>

<p>This needs to be changed to a stateful parser that considers:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
,dc=
, DC=
;DC=
; dc=
... etc
</code></pre>

<p>Originally reported <a href="http://framework.zend.com/wiki/display/ZFUSER/Zend_Auth_Adapter_Ldap+Operator%27s+Guide?focusedCommentId=42013#comment-42013">here</a>.</p>

